{
  "about": {
    "slides": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "text": "<p>Hello there. This is <strong>Reframed</strong>—A Digital inspiration LAB</p>",
        "actions": [
          {
            "goto": 2,
            "label": "What is its purpose?"
          },
          {
            "goto": 4,
            "label": "Whathever, not interested"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 2,
        "text": "<p>\"Reframed\" is here for the exploration and analysis of visual design work, and to discover what makes it effective.</p><p>True originality is a myth. Everyone is influenced and inspired by something.</p><p>Acting on that knowledge means creating new work that evokes a fresh perspective on existing inspiration.</p>",
        "actions": [
          {
            "goto": "/examples",
            "label": "So, how do you show that “Fresh perspective”?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 3,
        "text": "<p>We’ll show what influences us and how final result looks like. This is exercise to make this influence more conscious and use it as a tool for finding inspiration in our references. We call this reframing.</p>",
        "actions": [
          {
            "goto": "/examples",
            "label": "Got it, let’s see what you got. GO TO Examples."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 4,
        "text": "<p>So yoU’re more “show, don’t tell” type of person? then you can check examples page, and see how inspiration influences design work.</p>",
        "actions": [
          {
            "goto": "/examples",
            "label": "Got it"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
